def sniff(df):
    with pd.option_context('display.max_columns', 20):
        info = pd.DataFrame()
        info['DataType'] = df.dtypes
        info['Missing Count'] = df.isnull().sum().values
        info['Missing %'] = (df.isnull().mean().values * 100).round(2)
        info['Unique Count'] = df.nunique().values
        info['Unique Values'] = df.apply(pd.Series.unique).values
        return info.sort_values(by='DataType', ascending=True)

             '45-49', '50-54', '55-59', '60-64', '65-69', '70-74', '75-79', '80-84', '85+']

    'CI5_continent': {idx+1: name for idx, name in enumerate(['Africa', 'South America', 'North America', 'Asia', 'Europe', 'Oceania'])},

# Group by year to see overall trends
df_by_year = df_cleaned.groupby('year').agg(
    total_cases=('cases', 'sum'),
    total_py=('py', 'sum')
).reset_index()

# Calculate overall incidence rate per year
df_by_year['overall_incidence_rate'] = (df_by_year['total_cases'] / df_by_year['total_py']) * 100000

plt.figure(figsize=(14, 6))

plt.title('Overall Cancer Incidence Rate Over Time')

plt.xlabel('Year')

df_all_cancers = sample[sample['cancer'] == 'All cancers excluding non-melanoma skin']

)

# Select only the key numerical columns for the correlation matrix
numerical_df = sample[['cases', 'py', 'year', 'incidence_rate']]

# Calculate the correlation matrix
corr_matrix = numerical_df.corr()

# Plot the heatmap
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 7))
sns.heatmap(
    corr_matrix,
    annot=True,     # Show the correlation values on the map
    fmt='.2f',      # Format the values to 2 decimal places
    cmap='vlag',    # Use a diverging colormap (blue = negative, red = positive)
    vmin=-1,        # Set the color scale min to -1
    vmax=1,         # Set the color scale max to +1
    linewidths=.5   # Add lines between cells
)
plt.title('Correlation Heatmap of Numerical Variables')
plt.show()
